<HEADLINE>
<P>
NATIONAL ROUNDUP; 
</P>
<P>
MISTAURIAN EASILY WINS VAGRANCY 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
From Associated Press 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Mistaurian joined the leaders entering the stretch, then drew away to a 7 
1/4-length victory over Feel The Beat in the $83,400 Vagrancy Handicap Sunday 
at Belmont Park. 
</P>
<P>
Ridden by Herb McCauley and carrying 113 pounds, Mistaurian had to go wide at 
the turn but easily won the race for older fillies and mares, returning $9.40, 
$3.80 and $2.10. 
</P>
<P>
Feel The Beat, ridden by Chris Antley, led until Mistaurian's move and was 
three-quarters of a length ahead of favorite Fantastic Find under Craig Perret 
in the field of five. Spotty Hot and Wonchindordor were the trailers. 
</P>
<P>
Mistaurian, owned by Bernard Chaus, covered seven furlongs on a fast track in 
1:25 1/5. Her third victory in six starts this year was worth $50,040. 
</P>
<P>
Jockey Rick Moss suffered an ankle injury when his mount, Phoenix Sunshine, 
stumbled and fell, causing two other horses to go down during the $109,900 
Locust Grove at Churchill Downs. 
</P>
<P>
Dibs, with Aaron Gryder aboard, was well outside the pileup and drew off for a 
two-length victory over City Crowds. 
</P>
<P>
Dibs covered the 1 1/8 miles over the turf in 1:50 3/5 and paid $15.80, $5.60 
and $2.80. 
</P>
<P>
Clever Trevor, ridden by Don Pettinger, made his turf debut a successful one at 
Arlington International Racecourse, winning a $28,000 allowance race over one 
mile in 1:36.1. 
</P>
<P>
The victory was the second in a row this year for Clever Trevor and increased 
his lifetime record to 12 victories in 19 starts. He has earned $1.05 million. 
</P>
</TEXT>
