<HEADLINE>
<P>
SUSPECT IN FIRE FATAL TO THREE MEN IS FREED 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
A man who had been held for questioning in the deaths of three transients whose 
bodies were found in a fire at a boarded-up bar in Torrance was released by 
police Sunday morning after it was determined the blaze was probably 
accidental. 
</P>
<P>
The unidentified man was booked on suspicion of murder and arson shortly after 
the fire broke out Saturday morning at the Key Largo Bar at 17430 Prairie Ave. 
He was released at about 9 a.m. 
</P>
<P>
Names of the victims, three men in their mid-20s, were not released pending 
positive identification by the coroner's office. 
</P>
</TEXT>
<SUBJECT>
<P>
