<P>
TYPHOON LASHES PALAU, HEADS FOR PHILIPPINES 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By Associated Press 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<DATELINE>
<P>
MANILA 
</P>
</DATELINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Typhoon Percy battered the Pacific island of Palau and then roared west Sunday 
toward the Philippines, where at least 30 people were killed in a tropical 
storm last week. 
</P>
<P>
One child was killed on Palau, a newspaper said. 
</P>
</TEXT>
<TYPE>
<P>
