<HEADLINE>
<P>
JOSEPH MURUMBI; FORMER VICE PRESIDENT OF KENYA 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Joseph Murumbi, 79, vice president of Kenya under the young country's first 
president, Jomo Kenyatta. 
</P>
<P>
Educated in Bangalore, India, Murumbi was a career diplomat and politician, 
working in Somalia and London, and serving as assistant secretary of the 
Movement for Colonial Freedom when Kenya was a British colony. After 
independence, he was a member of the Kenya House of Representatives, minister 
of state, minister of external affairs and, in 1966, vice president. On Friday 
in Nairobi, after a long illness. 
</P>
