<P>
HIKER SLIPS, IS KILLED IN ANGELES FOREST FALL 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
A Long Beach man hiking in the Williams Canyon area of the Angeles National 
Forest fell 250 feet to his death as he attempted to climb a cliff, sheriff's 
deputies said Sunday. 
</P>
<P>
Ira Lee Crouser, 40, was hiking with his girlfriend when he slipped from the 
cliff about 6:30 p.m. Saturday. About 75 people witnessed Crouser's fall. 
</P>
<P>
Sheriff's deputies flew to the scene by helicopter and a doctor pronounced 
Crouser dead. 
</P>
<P>
"He was not an experienced hiker and he just slipped and fell," Sgt. Robert 
Dearmore said. 
</P>
