<P>
WILLIAM H. GRISHAW; FOUNDED CAMPS FOR DIABETICS 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Dr. William H. Grishaw, 87, specialist in diabetes who founded UniBetic Camps 
for Southern California young people suffering from diabetes. 
</P>
<P>
Grishaw believed strongly in educating young diabetics to manage their disease. 
He operated the camping program in the San Bernardino Mountains from 1946 until 
it ended in 1976. A former chief of staff and medical director of the Hospital 
of the Good Samaritan, he was president of the American Diabetes Assn. in 
1972-73 and helped organize the group's California chapter. On Wednesday in Los 
Angeles. 
</P>
