<HEADLINE>
<P>
FBI AGENT, TROOPER FOUND IN SMALL PLANE'S WRECKAGE 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By Associated Press 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<DATELINE>
<P>
GREENVILLE, Me. 
</P>
</DATELINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
The bodies of an FBI agent and a Massachusetts state trooper were found Sunday 
in the wreckage of a small plane atop a mountain ridge in western Maine, a 
search and rescue official said. The missing Piper Cherokee vanished in rough 
weather late last Monday, but FBI agent Paul Cavanagh and Trooper Joseph 
Moynihan were not declared missing until Friday, said a Maine Warden Service 
spokesman. 
</P>
</TEXT>
