<HEADLINE>
<P>
WOMAN ATTACKED AT EL CAJON SCHOOL 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
A 24-year-old El Cajon woman was sexually assaulted over the weekend on the 
grounds of an El Cajon school, police said. 
</P>
<P>
The woman was confronted by a man with a knife as she walked by Naranca 
Elementary at 10:30 p.m. Saturday, said police. The man forced the woman to a 
remote area of the campus, where he sexually assaulted her with a foreign 
object, then robbed her of $4 in cash. 
</P>
<P>
The assailant was described as a white or Latino male about 5 feet 4 inches 
tall, weighing about 165 pounds, with short, dark hair and dark-rimmed glasses. 
</P>
</TEXT>
