Show of Masters: Eighty-six Old Master drawings from Italy, France and the 
Netherlands, including works by Raphael and Rembrandt, went on display Sunday 
at the National Gallery Art in Washington. The show was selected from the 
drawings collection of the National Gallery of Scotland in Edinburgh and will 
be displayed through Sept. 23. GREG BRAXTON 
