<TEXT>
<P>
'Bull Durham II' Up to Bat: It's time to do the "wave," "Bull Durham" fans. 
</P>
<P>
Orion Pictures has approved a sequel to the 1988 baseball hit. "We intend to 
make a sequel to 'Bull Durham,' " producer Thom Mount told the Durham Morning 
Herald in North Carolina. Writer-director Ron Shelton is working on the 
screenplay, and original stars Kevin Costner, Susan Sarandon and Tim Robbins 
have been approached about signing on. The sequel would feature the three 
central "Bull Durham" characters in the latter stages of their lives. GREG 
BRAXTON 
