<HEADLINE>
<P>
VENTURA COUNTY NEWS ROUNDUP: OXNARD; 
</P>
<P>
MENTAL HEALTH CLINIC LOCATION SELECTED 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By KAREN McKEAN 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
An Oxnard location for a branch office of the Ventura County Mental Health 
Department has been found, and the County Board of Supervisors is expected to 
sign the lease Tuesday. 
</P>
<P>
The site -- a vacant J.C. Penney store at 555 S. A St. -- will house 10 health 
care specialists, who will take care of the medical and counseling needs of 
about 75 clients. 
</P>
<P>
The Oxnard team is part of the county's Small Community Outreach Treatment and 
Support (SCOTS) program, funded by a $16-million state grant for development of 
a prototype for mental health care systems in the state. 
</P>
<P>
"We chose this site because it was close to the Oxnard Transportation Center," 
said Ray Holzer, who found the property for the county. "Most of the people who 
use this system take a bus, and the transportation center is practically across 
the street." 
</P>
<P>
Once the lease is signed, $80,000 worth of renovations and construction will be 
needed before the team can begin providing service. Holzer said it should be 
ready to open by late August. KAREN McKEAN 
</P>
</TEXT>
