<P>
SIEBE $656 MILLION BUYS FOXBORO 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
From Times Wire Services 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<DATELINE>
<P>
LONDON 
</P>
</DATELINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Siebe PLC, a British security systems engineering group, has agreed to acquire 
Foxboro Co., a U.S.-based manufacturing equipment maker, for $656 million, the 
companies said today. 
</P>
<P>
Siebe is offering $52 a share for Foxboro's 12.62 million outstanding shares, 
the companies said. 
</P>
<P>
Foxboro stock soared on the news, rising $12.75 to $50.87 1/4 a share in early 
New York Stock Exchange trading. 
</P>
